I'd like to share my knowledge on Typescript.

This talk is going to be all about modules and imports.

This is all stuff that's good to know as a typescript developer.
However, a lot of this talk will be about things other than typescript, such as:

- Your browser
- Node
- Yarn Plug'n'Play
- PNPM

You'll learn how the module system really works.

These are all runnable examples. I encourage you to check out this repository and try them yourself!

More reading:

- A horrifically deep dive into TypeScript module resolution: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MEl2R7mEAP8&t=1s
- Total Typescript online course: https://www.totaltypescript.com/
